Grand Festival for National Reunification Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- A grand festival for national reunification to mark the 7th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration was opened in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony of the festival was held in front of Nam Gate in Mt. Taesong Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As representatives from the north and the south of Korea and abroad entered the venue of the opening ceremony following a large Korean Peninsula flag, working people in Pyongyang warmly welcomed them, chanting slogans for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The opening ceremony was attended by a delegation of the North Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration led by its Chairman An Kyong Ho, a delegation of the south side committee led by its Chairman Paek Rak Chong and a delegation of the overseas side committee led by Co-chairmen Kwak Tong Ui and Mun Tong Hwan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The large Korean Peninsula flag was hoisted with due ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An Kyong Ho in his opening speech said that the current festival would provide an occasion of strikingly demonstrating at home and abroad the unshakable will of the Koreans to defend and implement the June 15 joint declaration and thus reunify the country and the might of the nation united close as one under the banner of "By our nation itself". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed congratulatory speeches by Vice-President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Kim Yong Dae, Honorary Chairman Ri Ji Gwan and Co-Chairman Mun Tong Hwan of the South Side's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members of the three delegations enjoyed an art performance given by the Mansudae Art Troupe at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the evening the North Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration hosted a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture in honor of the delegations of the south and overseas sides.

Kim Jong Il Highly Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- A seminar was held in Cambodia and a reading session and a lecture took place in Democratic Congo on June 5 and 7 on the occasion of the 43rd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the secretariat of the chairman of the Funcinpec Party of Cambodia, addressing the seminar, said that Kim Jong Il has developed the WPK into an invincible revolutionary party and the DPRK into a genuine popular country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Democratic Congo said at the reading session on the "Short Biography of Comrade Kim Jong Il" that the leader has performed immortal exploits for the Korean revolution and cause of global independence and evinced his resolution to further intensify the study and dissemination of the Juche idea in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of Kinshasa Vocational School of Democratic Congo in his lecture referred in detail to the facts that the leader made the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung, the Juche idea shine as a permanent guiding idea of humankind through his energetic ideological and theoretical activities and wrought world-startling miracles with his indefatigable Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the functions watched Korean films including "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Work in Various Fields" and "Care Shown to Make Their Lives Shine ".

Repeal of "Agreement" on Sharing Funds for Upkeep of U.S. Forces Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification and the Committee to Deal with U.S. Forces Affairs of the Lawyers Association for Democratic Society of south Korea reportedly held a joint press conference in front of the building of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade in Seoul on June 5, at which they demanded the repeal of the "agreement" on sharing the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the press conference accused the south Korean authorities of holding negotiations with the U.S. allegedly on the issue of "improving the system of sharing the expenses for the upkeep of the U.S. forces".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference said that what the U.S. seeks in the current negotiations is to include a clause concerning the expenses for the relocation of U.S. forces in the agreement on sharing the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in a bid to secure a legal lever for forcing south Korea to cover the expenses for the relocation of the U.S. Second Division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging the National Assembly to fully investigate the legalization of the spending for the relocation of the U.S. Second Division, an attempt to increase the share of "defence spending", etc. and punish those responsible for the moves, the press release strongly demanded the "government" repeal the "agreement" itself.

German and Indian Embassy Officials Help Korean Farmers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- German Ambassador to the DPRK Friedrich Ludwig Loehr and his embassy officials gave a helping hand to the farmers of the DPRK-Germany Friendship Sunan Farm in Sunan District, Pyongyang, in weeding on a maize field on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During break the guests talked with officials of the farm, deepening friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day Charge d'Affaires a.i. Ram Lal Negi and staff members of the Indian embassy here helped the farmers of the DPRK-India Friendship Kalchon Cooperative Farm in Nampho City in weeding on a maize field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During break the guests enjoyed an art performance of schoolchildren and talked with officials of the farm about boosting the friendly relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staff members of the German and Indian embassies handed aid materials to the relevant farms.

Study Tour to Revolutionary Battle Sites in Mt. Paektu Area 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hyesan, June 13 (KCNA) -- The study tour of youth and children from across the country to the revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt. Paektu, which was started on the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the victorious Pochonbo battle, came to a close on June 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the tour the marchers laid floral baskets and bouquets before the statues of President Kim Il Sung in the shores of the River Karim and Lake Samji and the Chongbong Bivouac and the mosaic portraying the images of the three generals of Mt. Paektu built in the secret camp in Mt. Paektu and paid a tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On June 4 the marchers left Hyesan and arrived in Pochonbo. There they went round the command post where Kim Il Sung led the Pochonbo battle to victory 70 years ago, a police substation and a sub-county office of the Japanese imperialists, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they went to Samjiyon through Posori Spring, Junghung Table Land and the Phothae Revolutionary Site. On June 6 they toured the Samjiyon Grand Monument and other revolutionary relics, the Paektu Hall, the Chonji Health Complex, the Samjiyon Schoolchildren's Palace and other various places in Samjiyon town area changed beyond recognition and gave an art performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They passed through the secret camps on Mts. Sono and Kom before coming to the secret camp in Mt. Paektu on June 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There they visited the old home of Kim Jong Il and looked round with keen interest the historic relics preserved at the simple log cabin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day they held a story-telling on revolutionary legends associated with the old home in front of the Ode Monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They toured the Konchang Bivouac, the Chongbong Bivouac and the Rimyongsu Revolutionary Site on June 12.

Chief of Pyongyang Mission of AINDF Interviewed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Chief Jo Il Min of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front was interviewed by KCNA on Wednesday on the occasion of the 7th anniversary of the historic June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that there took place the historic Pyongyang summit, the first of its kind since the country's division, which culminated in the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, a landmark of independent national reunification, adding that this eye-opening event was the fruition of the fixed will and outstanding leadership of Kim Jong Il to present a reunified country to the Korean nation so as to fulfill the behests of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the facts that the reverence for Kim Jong Il is growing stronger among south Koreans as the days go by and they are becoming more vocal in their support to the Songun policy pursued by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Feeling uneasy and fearful of the south Koreans unanimously revering and following Kim Jong Il, the U.S. imperialists and their followers are working hard to bring back the June 15 era when the whole nation is advancing in firm unity, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have kept the south Korean people under the yoke of unbearable colonial slavery since their occupation of south Korea. They are working hard to install a pro-U.S. regime there by whipping together remnants of the military fascist dictatorship and wire-pulling them behind the scene, while perpetrating ceaseless moves for a war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 joint declaration can neither be implemented nor can the reunification of the country be achieved as long as the U.S. and its lackeys the pro-U.S. conservative forces including the "Grand National Party" are allowed to go on the rampage to bring back to south Korea the dark period of the fascist dictatorship and the Cold War era of confrontation with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The patriotic people in the south are waging a strenuous struggle to oust foreign forces from south Korea and shatter the moves of the pro-U.S. conservative forces to return to power under the slogan of a great alliance against the U.S. and conservatism as they are well aware of the U.S. imperialists' true colors as aggressors and the fascist and anti-reunification nature of the GNP through history and their bitter experiences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As they are led by Kim Jong Il, a peerless patriot and the great Songun brilliant commander, the Koreans will emerge victorious in the struggle to implement the June 15 joint declaration and surely greet the day of glory when they live a happy life holding in high esteem the sun of Songun in the reunified country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vanguard fighters and patriotic people from all walks of life in south Korea will step up their dynamic march for independent reunification under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself," cherishing the immense national pride of holding in high esteem Kim Jong Il who ushered in the June 15 era of reunification.

Inheritance of Spirit of June Resistance Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Ryu Son Min, chairperson of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils, reportedly issued a statement on June 10, calling for inheriting the spirit of the June resistance and achieving genuine democracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that 20 years have passed since the massive anti-U.S., anti-fascist resistance of the people of all social strata was waged in protest against the system of colonial military fascist dictatorship of the U.S. imperialists and their stooges in June 1987, the statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June people's resistance under the slogans "down with dictatorship" and "oust U.S. imperialists" left to the youth and students the bloody lesson that genuine democracy could not be won without independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is high time an end was put to the domination and interference of the U.S. imperialists and independence, peace and reunification were achieved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The youth and students at present are facing the important task to wage an extensive struggle to have a peace agreement signed and the "National Security Law" scrapped, check the conclusion of the "Free Trade Agreement", get the U.S. forces withdrawn from south Korea and dissolve the "Grand National Party" and thus achieve national independence by inheriting the spirit of the June resistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The youth and students will wage a dynamic struggle for true independence, democracy and reunification of this land.

Piffle of S. Korean Conservative Media Debunked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The joint press release that came at the end of the 21st inter-Korean ministerial talks gave assurances that the inter-Korean relations would be lifted to a higher stage in the spirit of "By our nation itself" in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean conservative media including Dong-A Ilbo and Munhwa Ilbo, taking issue with this, got overheated in misleading public opinion, arguing that "By our nation itself" is a "political expression of the north's strategy toward the south".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Thursday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This can never be tolerated, being a treacherous folly of denying the June 15 joint declaration, the milestone of reunification common to the nation, and fanning up confrontation between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "By our nation itself" is a great proposition in the era of independent reunification clearly laid down in the June 15 joint declaration and a noble patriotic idea unanimously supported by the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some south Korean conservative media, however, departing from the stand of the press, are decrying the idea of "By our nation itself", the landmark in the June 15 era of reunification, whipping up inter-Korean confrontation and throwing a wet blanket over the reconciliation and unity of the nation. This shows that they are trumpeters on the payroll of the aggressive outside forces and reactionary conservative forces including the Grand National Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The media of the era of "By our nation itself" should and must publish articles promoting the reconciliation and unity of the fellow countrymen and encouraging the movement for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no room in the June 15 era of reunification for the phony media unburdening themselves of a nasty spate of delirium, ignorant of the interests of the nation and the desire of the fellow countrymen.

Great Life of Kim Chol Ju
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Kim Chol Ju, an ardent revolutionary, turned a brilliant page in the history of the Korean revolution for his great life showing the philosophical principle of the revolutionary confidence which still seizes firmly the heart of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was born in Mangyongdae on June 12, Juche 5 (1916) as the second son of Kim Hyong Jik, an outstanding leader of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea, and Kang Pan Sok, an indomitable revolutionary fighter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He left the native home village in his early years following his parents and spent his childhood in Kangdong of Korea and Linjiang, Badaogou, Fusong, Antu and other parts of China.  He keenly experienced the sorrow and misfortune of a ruined nation, cultivating hatred for the Japanese imperialists and the spirit of resistance to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deep care and guidance of President Kim Il Sung were the wherewithal and nutritive elements by which he could grasp the truth of the revolution and grow to be a true revolutionary with an indomitable fighting spirit, stubborn will and noble traits and virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He devoted himself to the cause for the fatherland and nation with a firm faith that the Korean revolution was sure to win under the leadership of the President and the liberation of the country and the final victory of the revolution could be achieved only when protecting him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took as the maxim the speech of the President at the Mingyuegou Meeting held in December 1931 and made all efforts he could to successfully accelerate the work with the Chinese Anti-Japanese National Salvation Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deceived by the Japanese imperialists' national alienation policy and pernicious propaganda, the Chinese anti-Japanese units ill thought about Korean revolutionaries.  He boldly went among the units and led them to unswervingly take the true road of anti-Japanese struggle with his flawless Chinese and speech, flexible tactics and extraordinary knowledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also awakened intellectuals, handicraftsmen, small traders and even minor landlords as well as workers and peasants in the Antu area to rally them under the anti-Japanese banner and render positive support to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, thus making a prominent contribution to consolidation of mass foundation for the anti-Japanese armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Chol Ju died a heroic death at a sudden encounter with enemies near Chechangzi on June 14, 1935. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was, indeed, an indomitable revolutionary soldier who upheld President Kim Il Sung with his confidence and obligation.

Safety of Blood Transfusion Ensured in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The DPRK is making an earnest effort to ensure the safety of blood transfusion according to the program of the World Health Organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Safe blood transfusion has been raised as a key problem in the improvement of public health and prevention of epidemics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A regular state blood service system has been established in the country many years ago so as to guarantee the safety of people's lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the basis of it, the government has paid attention to increasing the number of voluntary unpaid blood donors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And it is training competent blood experts, while organizing regular information activities to give the people new understandings on blood transfusion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is organizing colorful events on the occasion of the "World Blood Donor Day" (June 14) to give pride and honor to those who voluntarily donate their blood free of charge.
 Beautiful deeds of people who donate their blood and skin to patients without hesitation have been reported from different parts of the country and the ranks of voluntary unpaid blood donors for over 20 years are on a steady increase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government has worked out "State Detailed Regulations on Blood Transfusion" and "Directory on Blood Transfusion". In accordance with them, examination of infectious factors is thoroughly undertaken, with the result that affluent and safe blood is supplied to the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to set up a working system for ensuring the quality in blood transfusion, "Technical Directory of GMP and GLP for Safety of Blood Transfusion" has been advanced recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The public health sector of the country is strengthening collaboration with the WHO and other international organizations, keeping close ties with them to ensure the safety of blood transfusion.

World Blood Donor Day Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Various events are taking place on the occasion of the "World Blood Donor Day" (June 14) in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A function on the "World Blood Donor Day" was co-sponsored by the DPRK Ministry of Public Health, World Health Organization and International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies at the People's Palace of Culture on June 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials of public health, ministries and national institutions, voluntary unpaid blood donors and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Pong Hun, vice-minister of Public Health, made an opening address.  He said that blood transfusion is an essential and important work in the field of public health that can save the lives of the human beings and referred to increasing the number of the voluntary unpaid blood donors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was followed by the acting representative of WHO here and head of the delegation of the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies working in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lecture on voluntary unpaid blood donation was given on the occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round the photos showing the successes in the blood transfusion sector. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this day, the souvenirs prepared by the World Health Organization and the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies were conveyed to those who have donated their blood free of charge for over 20 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar activities were made in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Varied propaganda activities are being conducted on this occasion in accordance with the theme for the year "Safe Blood for Safe Motherhood".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mass media of the DPRK are introducing those who donated their blood for the society and people and the beautiful deeds of medical workers.

National Workshop Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- A national workshop on trademark, industrial design and appellation of origin took place at the People's Palace of Culture on June 13 and 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials of the ministries and national institutions and experts of different units and the delegation of the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO) led by Mpazi Sinjela, dean of the WIPO Worldwide Academy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Song Guk, vice-director of the State Bureau for Quality Control, made a speech at the workshop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, briefings on the WIPO and the state bureau were given. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made under such titles as "On the Madrid System on the International Registration of Trademark and Experience of the DPRK", "On the Hague Agreement on International Registration of Industrial Designs and Experience of the DPRK", "On the DPRK's System for Protecting Appellation of Origin", "On Importance of Trademark, Industrial Design and Appellation of Origin in the Present World Economy".

Officials of ITF and Taekwon-Do Bodies Here
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Pak Jong Su, vice-president of the International Taekwon-Do Federation, and his party, the chairman of the European Taekwon-Do Federation and his party, the chairman of the Chinese Taekwon-Do Association and other persons concerned with Taekwon-Do and martial arts arrived here today to attend commemorations of the 5th death anniversary of former President of ITF Choe Hong Hui. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Flying into Pyongyang earlier were Leong Wai Meng, vice-president of ITF, and a delegation of the British Taekwon-Do Association.

Rodong Sinmun condena algunas prensas surcoreanas
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 14 de junio (ATCC) -- En la 21a ronda de las Conversaciones a Nivel de Ministro Norte-Sur de Corea fue publicado un comunicado conjunto ratificando la voluntad de llevar a una etapa mas alta en lo adelante las relaciones bilaterales conforme al espiritu del ideal de "Entre nosotros, los connacionales".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al cuestionarlo, los periodicos "Tong-a Ilbo" y "Munhwa Ilbo" y otros medios surcoreanos de corte conservador difunden versiones erroneas insistiendo en que ese ideal es la "expresion politica de la estrategia del Norte sobre el Sur".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto es un imperdonable acto antinacional que niega la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio, hoja de ruta comun de toda la nacion hacia la reunificacion, y busca la confrontacion fratricida entre ambas partes coreanas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual de este jueves y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  "Entre nosotros, los connacionales" es el axioma de la actual epoca de reunificacion independiente, que fue indicado claramente en la citada Declaracion Conjunta. Ademas, deviene el noble ideal signado del patriotismo y el amor a la nacion, apoyado y consentido unanimemente por la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sin embargo, algunos medios de prensa conservadores, al abandonar su postura de principios, denigran el citado ideal, fomentan el enfrentamiento con el Norte y congelan la reconciliacion y la unidad de la nacion, lo cual demuestra que ellos funcionan como plumiferos pagados al servicio de las fuerzas foraneas agresoras y las conservadoras reaccionarias como el "Gran Partido Nacional".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los medios de prensa de esta epoca de "Entre nosotros, los connacionales" deberan escribir los articulos, que contribuyan a lograr la reconciliacion y la unidad de la nacion y a impulsar el movimiento por la reunificacion independiente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los seudomedios de prensa, que propagan disparates sin saber cuales son los intereses de su nacion ni distinguir la aspiracion nacional, no tienen derecho a subsistir en esta era de reunificacion del 15 de Junio.

Diplomaticos alemanes e indios realizan trabajo voluntario
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 14 de junio (ATCC) -- El embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario Friedrich Ludwig Loehr y otros miembros de la Embajada de la Republica Federal de Alemania en Corea realizaron la vispera un trabajo voluntario para ayudar a los agricultores de la Granja de Amistad Corea-Alemania de Sunan del municipio homonimo de la capital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los huespedes desyerbaron con los granjeros en un maizal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los ratos de descanso ellos departieron con los funcionarios de la granja ensanchando la amistad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El mismo dia, hicieron lo mismo el encargado de negocios a.i. Ram Lal Negi y otros integrantes de la Embajada de la Republica de la India en Corea en la Granja Cooperativa de Amistad Corea-India de Kalchon de la ciudad de Nampho. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante el descanso, ellos vieron una funcion artistica de los ninos escolares y conversaron con los directivos de la granja sobre el desarrollo de las relaciones de amistad entre los dos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ellos entregaron los materiales de donacion a las respectivas granjas de amistad.

Grandiosa vida de Kim Chol Ju
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 14 de junio (ATCC) -- En la historia de la revolucion coreana esta grabada la brillante y apasionada vida del fervoroso revolucionario Kim Chol Ju. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Su grandiosa vida sigue conmoviendo hasta hoy al pueblo coreano porque demostro el valioso principio de la conviccion revolucionaria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Nacio el 12 de junio del 5 (1916) de la Era Juche en Mangyongdae como segundo hijo de Kim Hyong Jik, destacado dirigente del movimiento antijapones de liberacion nacional de Corea, y Kang Pan Sok, indoblegable combatiente revolucionaria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A su tierna edad tuvo que abandonar con sus padres su tierra natal y paso su infancia en Kangdong, Linjiang, Badaogou, Fusong, Antu, etc. donde experimento en carne propia la tristeza y la desgracia que acompanan a la nacion colonizada y se nutrio del gran odio y la rebeldia al imperialismo japones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La minuciosa direccion del Presidente Kim Il Sung le permitio percatarse de la verdad de la revolucion y crecer como autentico revolucionario con el indoblegable espiritu de lucha, la ferrea voluntad, y nobles virtudes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bien convencido de que la revolucion coreana saldra sin falta victoriosa si cuenta con el Presidente y se lograran la liberacion de la patria y la victoria final del proceso revolucionario cuando todos marchan apoyandole y defendiendole,Kim Chol Ju dedico todo lo suyo a la patria y la nacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, tomo por la maxima de su vida el discurso del Presidente pronunciado en la reunion de Mingyuegou convocada en diciembre de 1931 e hizo ingentes esfuerzos por fortalecer la colaboracion con el Ejercito antijapones de Salvacion Nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se infiltro en estas unidades antijaponesas, que hostilizaban a los revolucionarios coreanos, enganadas por la politica y la demagogia del imperialismo japones encaminadas a meter cunas entre la nacion coreana y la china, y logro conducirlas al verdadero camino de lucha antijaponesa apoyandose en su fluida elocuencia en chino, ingenios improvisados y excepcional sabiduria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, infundio la conciencia antijaponesa en los obreros, campesinos, intelectuales, artesanos, pequenos comerciantes y hasta en los terratenientes medianos y pequenos de la region de Antu, de modo que ellos apoyaran activamente la lucha revolucionaria antijaponesa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
ï¿½@De esta manera, realizo un aporte especial al fortalecimiento del terreno masivo de la lucha armada antijaponesa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras luchaba abnegadamente por la patria y la nacion, fallecio heroicamente el 14 de junio de 1935 en ese encuentro inesperado con los enemigos en las inmediaciones de Chechangzi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este indoblegable combatiente revolucionario dio el ejemplo de como apoyar al Presidente Kim Il Sung con la fe y obligacion moral.
